'''minasse''' is a [[Quenya]] noun meaning "fort, city, with a citadel and central watch-tower"<ref>{{VT|42}} p.24</ref>
==Etymology==
It derives from [[root]] [[MIN]] "one"<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}} p. 373</ref> and contains the common ending ''[[-asse]]''.

==Cognates==
*[[Sindarin]] ''[[minas]]''
